          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2015-08-04</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Promoting Opportunity for Disability Benefit Applicants Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends titles II (Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance) (OASDI) and XVI (Supplemental Security Income) (SSI) of the Social Security Act to authorize the Social Security Administration to give individuals denied OASDI and SSI benefits based on an adverse determination of disability any information on appropriate public or private entities that provide employment services, vocational rehabilitation services, or other support services.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-09-24T16:44:47Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
